            <title>[LU-14697] change performance-sanity to use mdtest</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14697</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;mdsrate&lt;/tt&gt; is an old test tool that was written by the Lustre developers for testing MDS performance, but it is not used by anyone.  It would be better to replace the use of &lt;tt&gt;mdsrate&lt;/tt&gt; in performance-sanity.sh with an equivalent &lt;tt&gt;mdtest&lt;/tt&gt; run, which is much more useful for exercising code that users will actually be running.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
